This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object attention and semantic segmentation. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a new network architecture to improve the quality of object attention. Additionally, it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with image analysis and processing. Finally, it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it proposes a new strategy for training neural networks.
